-- Charming Shoppes Surges on Report of Being Acquired
-- B y   M a t t   T o w n s e n d
-- 2012-05-01T23:07:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/charming-shoppes-surges-on-report-of-being-acquired.html
Charming Shoppes Inc. (CHRS) , owner of the
Lane Bryant clothing chain, surged on a report that  Ascena
Retail Group Inc. (ASNA)  will acquire it for $890 million.  The shares of Charming Shoppes, based in Bensalem,
Pennsylvania, jumped 20 percent to $7.10 at 7:02 p.m. in New
York. Ascena, based in Suffern, New York, rose 10 percent to
$21.  Ascena, owner of the Dressbarn clothing chain, will pay
$7.35 a share for Charming Shoppes, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing people familiar with the deal. The deal may be
announced tomorrow, the paper said. Representatives from both
companies didnâ€™t return calls or e-mails seeking comment.  Charming Shoppes hired Barclays Capital as a financial
adviser in December to conduct a financial review of the company
after more than four years of declining sales.  To contact the reporter on this story:
